    fact: 'Developed in France in the 1860s–80s, Impressionism shattered academic polish through outdoor painting (en plein air) and rapid, broken brushstrokes that captured fleeting light and atmosphere. The movement\'s name derived mockingly from Monet\'s "Impression, Sunrise" (1872). Monet\'s systematic series — haystacks, Rouen Cathedral, water lilies — studied how a single subject transforms across light conditions. Degas brought Japanese-print cropping and photographic angles to scenes of ballet and modern life. Key artists: Claude Monet, Edgar Degas, Pierre-Auguste Renoir, Camille Pissarro, Berthe Morisot.',
