    fact: 'Emerging in Counter-Reformation Rome c.1600, Baroque art dramatized religious narratives through violent light contrasts (tenebrism) and surging movement. Caravaggio placed biblical figures in street-level settings illuminated by a single dramatic source; his influence swept across Europe within a decade. In the Dutch Republic, Rembrandt used chiaroscuro to explore psychological depth in portraiture and biblical narrative; Vermeer captured domestic light with extraordinary optical sensitivity. Bernini\'s marble sculptures vibrate with theatrical emotion. Key artists: Caravaggio, Rembrandt, Vermeer, Rubens, Bernini, Artemisia Gentileschi.',
