    fact: 'Invented by Picasso and Braque between 1907–1914, Cubism dismantled Renaissance single-point perspective by showing objects from multiple simultaneous viewpoints, creating fragmented, faceted surfaces. Picasso\'s "Les Demoiselles d\'Avignon" (1907) — influenced by African masks and Cézanne\'s geometric analysis — announced the rupture. Analytic Cubism reduced the world to near-monochrome facets; Synthetic Cubism introduced collaged newspaper and pattern. Juan Gris, Fernand Léger, and Robert Delaunay extended the vocabulary. Key artists: Pablo Picasso, Georges Braque, Juan Gris, Fernand Léger.',
