    fact: 'Romanticism (c.1780–1850) rebelled against Enlightenment rationalism, exalting emotion, imagination, and the awesome power of nature. J.M.W. Turner dissolved ships and storms in vortices of light and color, anticipating abstraction by 50 years. Caspar David Friedrich\'s "Wanderer above the Sea of Fog" (1818) typifies Romantic spiritual yearning — a solitary figure before an infinite, misty void. Eugène Delacroix brought turbulent color to historical subjects; Francisco Goya confronted war\'s brutality with harrowing directness in "The Third of May 1808." Key artists: Turner, Friedrich, Delacroix, Goya, Géricault, Blake.',
