    q: 'Nietzsche described great art as arising from tension between the ordered Apollonian drive and which opposing force?',
    options: ['The Socratic drive', 'The Dionysian drive', 'The Platonic drive', 'The Kantian sublime'],
    answer: 1,
  },
  {
    category: 'Renaissance',
    q: 'Who painted the Sistine Chapel ceiling, working in sections of wet plaster over four years (1508–1512)?',
    options: ['Leonardo da Vinci', 'Raphael', 'Botticelli', 'Michelangelo'],
    answer: 3,
  },
  {
    category: 'Gallery',
    q: 'Raphael\'s "School of Athens" places which two philosophers at the geometric and philosophical center of the composition?',
    options: ['Socrates & Plato', 'Aristotle & Socrates', 'Plato & Aristotle', 'Hegel & Kant'],
    answer: 2,
