  {
    category: 'Philosophy',
    q: 'Kant described aesthetic judgment as "subjective yet" doing what — which makes it unique among judgments?',
    options: ['Always relative to culture', 'Claiming universal assent', 'Rooted purely in reason', 'Dependent on moral virtue'],
